==Distribution==
''Bedsitcom'' was distributed by the [[Channel Four Television Corporation]], who broadcast the show on its [[Channel 4|eponymous channel]]. It premi<U+00E8>red in the UK at 10:40&nbsp;p.m. on 8 December 2003.<ref name="Mark Lawson">{{Cite news|title=Saint Mum, Saint Doctor and the evil MMR|first=Mark|last=Lawson|authorlink=Mark_Lawson|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/media/2003/dec/08/tvandradio.columnists|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|publisher=[[Guardian News and Media]]|location=[[London]]|date=8 December 2003|issn=0261-3077|oclc=60623878|accessdate=12 November 2010}}</ref> Originally intended to run for eight weeks, ''Bedsitcom'' was taken off the air after only two, following poor ratings.{{Sfn|Piper|2004|p=283}} Its first four episodes were broadcast nightly until 11 December<U+2014>the fifth episode was shown on 15 December, with the final three episodes airing nightly until 18 December.<ref name="The Times"/> There are currently no plans to revive the series, and it is not available either on DVD or on [[4oD]], Channel 4's [[Video on demand|on demand]] service.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/tubetalk/a35946/im-sorry.html|title=I'm sorry|first=Neil|last=Wilkes|date=17 August 2006|publisher=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=12 November 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.channel4.com/programmes/4od/all#b|title=4oD: All programmes|year=2010|publisher=[[Channel 4]]|location=[[London]]|accessdate=1 December 2010}}</ref>

